# 5. 憧れを思い浮かべて

Turtle Plushie: ...
Nene: Excuse me...
Turtle Plushie: Huh? You're that person from earlier...
Nene: I'm sorry, but another turtle told me about what's been going on with you.
Nene: Your dream is to carry people across the river on your back, but you're too scared to swim in the water, right?
Turtle Plushie: Oh...
Turtle Plushie: I see.
Nene: ...
Nene: (Wh-What do I do now...? I didn't really think about how this conversation would go...)
Luka: Don't worry.
Nene: Huh...?
Luka: Just say what you feel, Nene, and everything should be fine.
Nene: Oh...
Nene: (Just say what I feel...?)
Nene: The thing is, I think I know what you're going through right now.
Turtle Plushie: What...?
Nene: I also have a dream. I want to become a world-class musical actress...
Nene: But... There was a time when I didn't think I could.
Turtle Plushie: You didn't think you could...? Why?
Nene: So...
Nene: (I can't remember my next line! What should I do? What should I do!)
Nene: I ended up ruining our show... Everyone was so sad and disappointed.
Nene: After that, I became too scared to stand on stage...
Turtle Plushie: But you're okay now?
Nene: Yeah, I'm not afraid of standing on stage anymore, but I still feel scared about a lot of things...
Turtle Plushie: Huh...?
Nene: The thought of performing in places I've never been before alongside people I'll be meeting for the first time is kinda scary to me...
Nene: And I've met some people who are so good that I've worried that I'll never be able to do what they can, even if I try.
Nene: But whenever I feel that way, I'm able to muster enough courage to keep moving forward...
Turtle Plushie: Courage...
Turtle Plushie: Where does that courage come from?
Nene: Where? A few different places...
Nene: My friends, for one, because of all the support they've given me. But also...
Little Mermaid: “♪————!”
Little Nene: ...!
Nene: I think about my hero... The person who gave me my dream. The person who showed me what I wanted to become.
Nene: And then I can keep moving forward, even when I'm scared.
Turtle Plushie: By thinking about your hero...?
Nene: I understand that you're scared.
Nene: But I'm sure you'll get closer to achieving your dream if you find the courage to take the next step forward.
Nene: So, please... If you still want to make your dream come true...
Nene: I'll help. So why don't we make it happen together?
Turtle Plushie: ...
Turtle Plushie: You're such an amazing person. If I can be just like you—
Plushie B: Thanks for the ride!
Plushie B: Riding on the back of a turtle was so much fun! I'll be back again soon!
Nene: Oh...
Turtle Plushie C: Sure thing! Come back soon!
Turtle Plushie: Those plushies look so happy...
Robo-Nene: Yes, they and the turtles all seem to be enjoying themselves very much.
Turtle Plushie: I wish...
Luka: Huh?
Turtle Plushie: I wish I could be like them...
Turtle Plushie: I want to carry everyone across, and have them feel happy like that...!
Luka: You do...?
Turtle Plushie: I... I...!
Turtle Plushie: I'll try. I'm still scared...
Turtle Plushie: But I'll give it a try...!
Nene: ...!
Nene: *Nod* I know you'll do great.
Robo-Nene: You can do it. The edge of the water is just right there.
Turtle Plushie: R-Right...!
Turtle Plushie: I-I'm not afraid. I can do this...
Turtle Plushie: *Gasp* N-Now, just dive in...
Luka: You can do it...!
Turtle Plushie: H-Here goes nothing!
Nene: Oh...!
Robo-Nene: He did it! He is in the water.
Turtle Plushie: I did it...! Look! I'm in the water!
Nene: Yeah, congratulations!
Robo-Nene: He looks stable in the water. I believe he should have no trouble carrying the other plushies across.
Turtle Plushie: O-Oh, about that... Can I ask you for a favor?
Luka: A favor?
Turtle Plushie: So, I'd like to try carrying someone across. If possible, would you be willing to ride on my back...?
Nene: Okay. Let's go for a ride.
Nene: Wh-Whoa... We're gliding across the water...!
Nene: Eep. The water's so cold...
Turtle Plushie: Yeah, but it feels really nice...!
Turtle Plushie: I never realized just how much fun it is to swim at full speed while carrying someone on my back...!
Nene: Hehe. I'm so glad for you.
Turtle Plushie: Thanks! Anyway, hang on tight...! I'll take you wherever you want!
Robo-Nene: Welcome back, you two. You both seemed to enjoy yourselves very much.
Nene: We did. That was my first time riding on a turtle's back, but it was really fun...
Luka: That was incredible. This means you should be able to carry everyone across to the other side now♪
Turtle Plushie: Thanks. I wouldn't have been able to work up the courage to do that if it weren't for you...!
Turtle Plushie: So, I should be fine now...! I feel like I can carry anyone across.
Robo-Nene: That is wonderful to hear.
Turtle Plushie: Oh, that reminds me... You guys wanted to go to the other side, right?
Turtle Plushie: Why don't I take you all across? I promise to do a good job!
Nene: You will? Thank you... That'd be incredibly helpful.
Nene: Actually, while we're at it, can we ask you for something else?
Turtle Plushie: Sure, what's up?
Nene: Would you also be willing to carry our friends across? There's quite a lot of us, if that's okay...
Turtle Plushie: No problem! It'd be great to carry so many people across!
Robo-Nene: Thank you very much. Then, I shall go let them know.
Luka: I'm so happy that our turtle friend's back in the water.
Nene: Me too... And thanks, Luka.
Luka: Oh? Did I do something worthy of being thanked?
Nene: You gave me the push I needed to help him.
Luka: I did? I honestly just said what I felt...
Luka: But I'm glad to hear that I was able to help you, Nene♪
Luka: *Yawn* Seeing everyone smile so much is making me sleepy for some reason...
Luka: Would you mind if I used your lap as a pillow, Nene?
Nene: Huh...? My lap? You plan on sleeping here?
Luka: Yes. Also, I'd like to sleep on our turtle's back as he swims. I have a feeling that I'll have a wonderful dream about swimming in the sea...
Luka: Zzz... Zzz...♪
Nene: Huh? She fell asleep while standing...?
Nene: (Still... I'm really glad that I could help him.)
Turtle Plushie: Alright, I'll practice swimming while we wait for your friends to get here!
Turtle Plushie: I'm still a little scared of the water... But I'm gonna keep trying my best...!
Nene: (Right.)
Nene: (The future's full of scary and not-so-nice things...)
Nene: (Not just the turtle's... Mine as well...)
Nene: (But...)
Nene: (I just have keep remembering my dream. My hero...)
Nene: (I have to maintain this courage and keep moving forward.)
